Comment.Text: The signal is then splitted in blocks of 1 second every 16th second and the logarithmic band power is computed thanks to the two Simple DSP and the Signal Average boxes.
The CSP Spatial Filter produced in the previous scenarios is used prior to the feature extraction.

Finally, the feature vectors are classified with an LDA classifier. In Analysis.xml the state vector of the classifier is sent to the Graz Visualization box for feedback.
In order to display correct feedback, the Graz Visualization box expects a negative value for one class and a positive value for the other class.

This scenario should be used after the CSP Spatial Filter and The LDA CLassifierfrom in the previous scenarios have been trained. This scenario is a real time fully working acquisition with visual feedback for the user.
With this scenario, you can watch the blue bar feedback showing how well you perform for a direction in real time.
The Python Scripting box allows for the connection with the Arduino Serial Monitor and to send messages that will active the Arduino code for Prosthetic control.
